                        Clubb
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1223</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1223</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-10-28T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1223">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Ward, Angus I.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-28">October 28,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received October 27—8:27 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1839. ReContel 1837, October 27. Following received late yesterday evening as
                    Mukden’s 89, 24th: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Consul General Ward, Rehberg, Tatsumi and two European employees removed
                            by police for 2 or 3 days connection their alleged as <pb facs="0998" n="988" xml:id="pg_988"/> sault Chinese employee. Sent Washington,
                            repeated Peiping 89. Stokes<note n="16" xml:id="d1223fn16">William N.
                                Stokes, Vice Consul at Mukden.</note> for Ward.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated hereby despite original routing provide against possible transmittal
                    delay.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 1839, Shanghai 1106.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
